Police spokeswoman Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said the vehicle crashed into the Burling Road house around 6.30am. The impact caused a wall to collapse on the children - aged between 10 and 14 - who were in bed. “A 10-year-old child died at the scene,” Mbhele said. A 12- and a 14-year-old were injured and taken to RK Khan Hospital to be treated. The cause of the accident was not known but a suspect was arrested and Chatsworth police were investigating a case of culpable homicide, Mbhele said. The Mercury